OL,3,CFacial recognition to be used in
OL,4,Cpolicing operation of protests and FA
OL,5,CCup final
OL,7,FStrict conditions have been placed on
OL,8,Fboth marches, with protesters having
OL,9,Fto follow certain routes at specified
OL,10,Ftimes, and to rally in specific
OL,11,Flocations: Unite the Kingdom starting
OL,12,Fin Kingsway and ending in Parliament
OL,13,FSquare, and Nakba Day starting in
OL,14,FExhibition Road in Kensington and
OL,15,Fending on Pall Mall.
OL,17,FMr Harman said that while some pro-
OL,18,FPalestine marches had made Jewish
OL,19,Fpeople feel unsafe, some Unite the
OL,20,FKingdom demonstrations had made
OL,21,FMuslims feel the same way.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1779120673
OL,3,CFacial recognition to be used in
OL,4,Cpolicing operation of protests and FA
OL,5,CCup final
OL,7,FPolice are expected to monitor slogans
OL,8,Fused and have been in discussions with
OL,9,Fprosecutors about language which has
OL,10,Fpreviously not been criminalised, but
OL,11,Fcould see protesters arrested.
OL,13,FRecent criminal cases have seen
OL,14,Fsuspects charged after shouting "death
OL,15,Fto the IDF (Israel Defence Forces)"
OL,16,Fand "globalise the intifada".
OL,26,@vD@aOUwD@cO]xD@EOUxD@\O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/11
